### Monitoring & Metrics Examples
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Basic Health Check (No Auth Required)
GET http://localhost:8000/health

### Expected Response
# HTTP/1.1 200 OK
# {
#   "status": "healthy",
#   "timestamp": "2025-12-16T23:00:00.000Z",
#   "uptime": 123.456,
#   "version": "1.0.0"
# }

### Detailed System Health (Auth Required)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/system/health
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response
# HTTP/1.1 200 OK
# {
#   "status": "healthy",
#   "timestamp": "2025-12-16T23:00:00.000Z",
#   "uptime": 123.456,
#   "memory": {
#     "used": 123456789,
#     "total": 987654321,
#     "percentage": 12.5
#   },
#   "cpu": {
#     "usage": 45.2,
#     "cores": 8
#   },
#   "services": {
#     "database": "healthy",
#     "cache": "healthy",
#     "messageQueue": "healthy"
#   }
# }

### System Metrics
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/system/metrics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Time Series Metrics
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/metrics/timeseries?metric=cpu&interval=1m
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Query Logs
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/metrics/logs?level=error&limit=100
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List System Events
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/metrics/events?type=deployment&since=2025-12-01
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Active Alerts
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/metrics/alerts?status=active
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### System Configuration
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/system/config
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Restart Service (Admin Only)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/system/restart
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "service": "scheduler",
  "graceful": true
}
